        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): render identity name in runtime prompt",
        "body": "## Summary\n- resolve the active agent identity.name into system prompt runtime metadata\n- render the configured identity as `agent=...` while keeping the technical slot id as `agentId=...` for debugging\n- add focused coverage for prompt params, runtime rendering, and CLI prompt assembly\n\nFixes #81269.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/system-prompt-params.test.ts src/agents/system-prompt.test.ts src/agents/cli-runner/helpers.system-prompt.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Runtime prompt metadata now prefers the configured agent identity name over the technical slot id, avoiding repeated `agent=main` persona drift when `identity.name` is set.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on this PR branch (`codex/runtime-identity-name-81269-reopen-20260618`) with repository dependencies available, exercising the agents prompt parameter, prompt rendering, and CLI prompt assembly paths through the repository test harness.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/system-prompt-params.test.ts src/agents/system-prompt.test.ts src/agents/cli-runner/helpers.system-prompt.test.ts --reporter=verbose\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: Terminal capture from the local OpenClaw agents prompt run showed the changed behavior:\n\n```text\n✓ |agents| src/agents/system-prompt-params.test.ts > buildSystemPromptParams > resolves configured identity name for the active agent\n✓ |unit-fast| src/agents/system-prompt.test.ts > buildAgentSystemPrompt > includes agent and session identity in runtime when provided\n✓ |agents| src/agents/cli-runner/helpers.system-prompt.test.ts > buildCliAgentSystemPrompt > includes session identity in runtime when provided\n\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  89 passed (89)\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  14 passed (14)\n[test] passed 2 Vitest shards in 6.51s\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The focused agents tests verify configured `identity.name` is resolved for the active agent and appears in runtime prompt identity metadata while the technical slot id remains available for session/debug context. `git diff --check` produced no output.\n\nWhat was not tested: A live agent conversation was not started in this environment; the focused prompt construction and CLI assembly paths above exercise the affected runtime prompt output.\n\n---\nReopened after active-PR limit cleanup. Supersedes closed PR #94397.\n\n\n\n## Additional proof for normalized agent ids\n\nAfter commit `8a83345a17`, I verified that a configured raw id still resolves when the runtime uses the normalized id.\n\nCommand:\n\n```text\nnode --import tsx -e 'import { buildSystemPromptParams } from \"./src/agents/system-prompt-params.ts\"; import { buildRuntimeLine } from \"./src/agents/system-prompt.ts\"; const { runtimeInfo } = buildSystemPromptParams({ config: { agents: { list: [{ id: \"Team Ops\", identity: { name: \"Ops Navigator\" } }] } }, agentId: \"team-ops\", runtime: { host: \"host\", os: \"darwin\", arch: \"arm64\", node: process.version, model: \"test-model\" } }); console.log(buildRuntimeLine(runtimeInfo));'\n```\n\nObserved output:\n\n```text\nRuntime: agent=Ops Navigator | agentId=team-ops | host=host | os=darwin (arm64) | node=v25.9.0 | model=test-model | thinking=off\n```\n\nFocused validation after the normalized-id fix:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/system-prompt-params.test.ts --reporter=dot\n# 1 file passed, 8 tests passed\n\ngit diff --check\n# no output\n```\n",
